description:
According to the present invention, it is desired that:

    (a) The oxide for preventing the diffusion of elements is an oxide containing Ce as a constituent element;
    (b) The oxide for preventing the diffusion of elements is a Ce composite oxide in which SmO3 is solidly dissolved in CeO2;
    (c) The Ce composite oxide has a molar composition represented by the following general formula:

(CeO2)1-x(SmO3/2)x

        wherein x is a number of 0<x≦0.3;


    (d) The inner layer of the oxygen electrode layer contains 10 to 30 mass % of the oxide for preventing the diffusion of elements and contains 70 to 90 mass % of the perovskite composite oxide;
    (e) The perovskite composite oxide is an (La, Sr)(Co, Fe)O3 oxide;
    (f) The inner layer of the oxygen electrode layer is formed having a thickness smaller than that of the surface layer; and
    (g) When the thickness of the inner layer is denoted by L1 and the thickness of the surface layer by L2, the inner layer and the surface layer of the oxygen electrode layer are so formed that an electrode function index W defined by the following formula (1):

W=W1+W2  (1)

        wherein W1 is an index expressed by n1·L1, W2 is an index expressed by n2·L2, n1 is a number of contacts per a unit length (10 μm) on the interface between the inner layer and the reaction-preventing layer, and n2 is a number of contacts per a unit length (10 μm) on the interface between the inner layer and the surface layer,

is 300 to 500.
